The Federation of Unions of South Africa has dismissed Dennis George as General Secretary. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Former secretary general of the Federation of Unions of South Africa (Fedusa) Dennis George has been dismissed. George is alleged to have acquired Ayo Technology shares through his company at a significantly reduced rate. He was suspended from Fedusa in February as the PIC's questionable R4,3-billion investment in Ayo was scrutinised at the PIC Inquiry. READ: Fedusa suspends Dennis George over Ayo scandal President of Fedusa Godfrey Selematsela stated that any suggestions of impropriety on its behalf are inaccurate and untested. George has stated he will communicate further through his legal representation. A final forensic report into the matter will be released at the end of May.